          "body": "The chapter ends with concentrated warnings. On *that day*, do not descend from the housetop or turn back from the field to retrieve your goods (v.31). *Remember Lot's wife* (v.32) — three words functioning as the chapter's tightest imperative. She did not return *to* sin; she looked *back at* what she was leaving, and judgment caught her mid-glance. Verse 33 stretches the principle to its widest: whoever seeks to keep his life will lose it; whoever loses it will preserve it. Then the dividing scenes — bed, mill, field — *one taken, one left* (vv.34-35). The disciples' question *where, Lord?* (v.37) receives the chapter's most enigmatic reply: *where the body is, there also the vultures will be gathered* — the day of revealing is itself the location, unmissable wherever judgment falls."
